          <p></p>
          <p><b>Some takeaways from the Vegas figures:</b> </p>
          <ol>
            <li><b>Denomination depends on location</b>.&nbsp; On the Strip=
, the
              best payouts are with the dollar machines (but that makes you=
 bet
              more than you would on a 1=C2=A2, 5=C2=A2, or 25=C2=A2 machin=
e, you'll lose more
              money, despite the higher return).&nbsp; Everywhere else, 5=
=C2=A2, 25=C2=A2,
              and $1 machines are pretty much the same.</li>
            <li><b>The strip has the worst payouts.</b>&nbsp; Downtown has
              historically been a bit better, though some years it=E2=80=99=
s a bit worse
              than the Strip.&nbsp; The Boulder Strip and North Las Vegas
              casinos have the best payouts.&nbsp; (=E2=80=9CNorth Las Vega=
s=E2=80=9D is not the
              north end of the Strip, it=E2=80=99s a separate city, north o=
f downtown
              Las Vegas.)</li>
            <li><b>The gap for downtown 5=C2=A2 between the reported payout=
s and the
                Wizard=E2=80=99s survey</b> is probably because the downtow=
n has a
              higher mix of video poker (which tends to pay better than slo=
ts),
              and the government reports lump slots and video poker togethe=
r.</li>
          </ol>
